<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-173-902  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 173 902.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  April 10 1989 n412 p19(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PCs turn to red ink at Tandon. (Tandon Corp)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Myers, Edith.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Tandon Corp is losing money in spite of impressive microcomputersales.andP;  The company posted a $19.8 million loss in 1988, about 11cents per share.andP;  This was in spite of a revenue of $309.3million, up from $17 million in 1987.andP;  Fourth quartermicrocomputer sales of $95 million could not counteract thefinancial loss.andP;  1988 revenue was adversely affected by DRAM chipshortages and inventory adjustments at year's end.andP;  The companyclosed its Chatsworth, CA headquarters in Sept 1988, consolidatingwith a Moorpark, CA manufacturing facility.andP;  The bulk of thecompany's microcomputer sales are in Europe.andP;  Chmn and CEO SirjangLal Jugi Tandon is once again in charge at the company.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tandon Corp. (finance).andO;Ticker:    TCOR.andO;Topic:     LossesMicrocomputers.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Jugi Tandon. (portrait)Person:    Tandon, Sirjang Lal (management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>